</p><p>He is a friend of President <a href="/wiki/Bill_Clinton" title="Bill Clinton">Bill Clinton</a>, having met Clinton before his presidency began. Spacey once described Clinton as "one of a shining light" in the political process.<sup id="cite_ref-abc_23-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-abc-23">&#91;23&#93;</a></sup> He additionally made a <a href="/wiki/Cameo_appearance" title="Cameo appearance">cameo appearance</a> in the short film <i>President Clinton: Final Days</i>, a light-hearted <a href="/wiki/Political_satire" title="Political satire">political satire</a> produced by the <a href="/wiki/Presidency_of_Bill_Clinton" title="Presidency of Bill Clinton">Clinton Administration</a> for the 2000 <a href="/wiki/White_House_Correspondents_Dinner" class="mw-redirect" title="White House Correspondents Dinner">White House Correspondents Dinner</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-newyorktimes_106-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-newyorktimes-106">&#91;106&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Spacey has undertaken activism in the domain of <a href="/wiki/HIV/AIDS" title="HIV/AIDS">HIV/AIDS</a>. In 2002, Spacey, actor <a href="/wiki/Chris_Tucker" title="Chris Tucker">Chris Tucker</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Jeffrey_Epstein" title="Jeffrey Epstein">Jeffrey Epstein</a> accompanied Bill Clinton on a trip throughout several African countries to promote AIDS awareness on the continent.<sup id="cite_ref-107" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-107">&#91;107&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-108" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-108">&#91;108&#93;</a></sup> He also participated in several fundraisers for HIV/AIDS healthcare, including <a href="/wiki/AmfAR" title="AmfAR">amfAR</a> Cinema Against AIDS in 2016<sup id="cite_ref-109" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-109">&#91;109&#93;</a></sup> and the 25th Annual <a href="/wiki/Elton_John_AIDS_Foundation_Academy_Award_Party" title="Elton John AIDS Foundation Academy Award Party">Elton John AIDS Foundation Academy Award Party</a> in 2017.<sup id="cite_ref-110" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-110">&#91;110&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Spacey met Venezuelan president <a href="/wiki/Hugo_Ch%C3%A1vez" title="Hugo Chávez">Hugo Chávez</a> in September 2007 but never spoke to the press about their encounter. During the trip, he visited the Venezuelan film studio <a href="/wiki/Villa_del_Cine" title="Villa del Cine">Villa del Cine</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-111" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-111">&#91;111&#93;</a></sup> In March 2011, following Belarusian president <a href="/wiki/Alexander_Lukashenko" title="Alexander Lukashenko">Alexander Lukashenko</a>'s crackdown on the <a href="/wiki/Belarusian_democracy_movement" class="mw-redirect" title="Belarusian democracy movement">Belarusian democracy movement</a>, Spacey joined <a href="/wiki/Jude_Law" title="Jude Law">Jude Law</a> in a street protest in London against Lukashenko's regime.<sup id="cite_ref-112" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-112">&#91;112&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>In October 2008, Spacey started the Kevin Spacey Foundation in the UK to encourage youth involvement in the arts.<sup id="cite_ref-113" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-113">&#91;113&#93;</a></sup> Headquartered in England and <a href="/wiki/Wales" title="Wales">Wales</a>, its purpose was to provide grants to individuals and organizations to help young people study the arts, particularly theatre.<sup id="cite_ref-114" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-114">&#91;114&#93;</a></sup> The charity shut down in February 2018 following sexual misconduct allegations against Spacey.<sup id="cite_ref-115" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-115">&#91;115&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>In September 2006, Spacey said that he intended to take up <a href="/wiki/British_citizenship" class="mw-redirect" title="British citizenship">British citizenship</a> when it is offered to him.<sup id="cite_ref-telegraph_116-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-telegraph-116">&#91;116&#93;</a></sup> When asked about the UK's <a href="/wiki/2016_United_Kingdom_European_Union_membership_referendum" title="2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum">2016 European Union membership referendum</a>, Spacey replied, "I appreciate you asking me the question, but I am not a British citizen, I am a resident of Great Britain. And I have never in my twelve years ever gotten involved in politics in Great Britain. I think it's inappropriate for me as a, really as a guest, in Great Britain, so I'll leave that to the British people."<sup id="cite_ref-117" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-117">&#91;117&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sexual_misconduct_allegations">Sexual misconduct allegations</span></h2>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1033289096"/><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">See also: <a href="/wiki/Weinstein_effect" title="Weinstein effect">Weinstein effect</a></div>
<p>On October 29, 2017, actor <a href="/wiki/Anthony_Rapp" title="Anthony Rapp">Anthony Rapp</a> alleged that Spacey, while appearing intoxicated, made a sexual advance toward him at a party in 1986, when Rapp was 14 and Spacey was 26.<sup id="cite_ref-HR_Nordyke_118-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-HR_Nordyke-118">&#91;118&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-NYDaily_Felman_119-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NYDaily_Felman-119">&#91;119&#93;</a></sup> Rapp had also shared this story in a 2001 interview with <i><a href="/wiki/The_Advocate_(LGBT_magazine)" class="mw-redirect" title="The Advocate (LGBT magazine)">The Advocate</a></i>, but Spacey's name was redacted from publication to avoid legal disputes and public <a href="/wiki/Outing" title="Outing">outing</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-120" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-120">&#91;120&#93;</a></sup> Spacey stated through Twitter that he did not remember the encounter, but that he owed Rapp "the sincerest apology for what would have been deeply inappropriate drunken behavior" if he had behaved as asserted.<sup id="cite_ref-IBT_Kanetkar_121-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-IBT_Kanetkar-121">&#91;121&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-122" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-122">&#91;122&#93;</a></sup> On September 9, 2020, Rapp sued Spacey for <a href="/wiki/Sexual_assault" title="Sexual assault">sexual assault</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sexual_battery" class="mw-redirect" title="Sexual battery">sexual battery</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Intentional_infliction_of_emotional_distress" title="Intentional infliction of emotional distress">intentional infliction of emotional distress</a> under the Child Victims Act.<sup id="cite_ref-Rapp_123-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Rapp-123">&#91;123&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Fifteen others then came forward alleging similar abuse,<sup id="cite_ref-124" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-124">&#91;124&#93;</a></sup> including <a href="/wiki/Boston" title="Boston">Boston</a> anchorwoman <a href="/wiki/Heather_Unruh" title="Heather Unruh">Heather Unruh</a>, who alleged that Spacey sexually assaulted her son;<sup id="cite_ref-Telegraph_301017_125-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Telegraph_301017-125">&#91;125&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-126" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-126">&#91;126&#93;</a></sup> filmmaker <a href="/wiki/Tony_Montana_(filmmaker)" title="Tony Montana (filmmaker)">Tony Montana</a>; actor Roberto Cavazos;<sup id="cite_ref-127" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-127">&#91;127&#93;</a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Richard_Dreyfuss" title="Richard Dreyfuss">Richard Dreyfuss</a>'s son Harry;<sup id="cite_ref-128" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-128">&#91;128&#93;</a></sup> and eight people who worked on <i>House of Cards</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-People_021117_129-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-People_021117-129">&#91;129&#93;</a></sup> <i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i> was contacted by "a number of people" who alleged that Spacey "groped and behaved in an inappropriate way with young men" as artistic director of the Old Vic.<sup id="cite_ref-Guardian_021117_130-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Guardian_021117-130">&#91;130&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-131" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-131">&#91;131&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-132" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-132">&#91;132&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Spacey also appears on flight logs from <a href="/wiki/Jeffrey_Epstein" title="Jeffrey Epstein">Jeffrey Epstein's</a> private jet from the early 2000s.<sup id="cite_ref-133" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-133">&#91;133&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Coming_out_controversy">Coming out controversy</span></h3>
<p>On the same day as Rapp's allegations against him, Spacey <a href="/wiki/Coming_out" title="Coming out">came out as gay</a> when apologizing to Rapp. He said, "I have had relationships with both men and women. I have loved and had romantic encounters with men throughout my life, and I choose now to live as a gay man."<sup id="cite_ref-134" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-134">&#91;134&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-guardian-convery_135-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-guardian-convery-135">&#91;135&#93;</a></sup> His decision to come out via his statement was criticized by gay celebrities, including <a href="/wiki/Billy_Eichner" title="Billy Eichner">Billy Eichner</a>, <a href="/wiki/George_Takei" title="George Takei">George Takei</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lance_Bass" title="Lance Bass">Lance Bass</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Wanda_Sykes" title="Wanda Sykes">Wanda Sykes</a>, as an attempt to change the subject and shift focus from Rapp's accusation, for using his own drunkenness as an excuse for making a sexual advance on a minor, and for implying a connection between homosexuality and <a href="/wiki/Child_sexual_abuse" title="Child sexual abuse">child sexual abuse</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-CNN_out_136-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CNN_out-136">&#91;136&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-137" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-137">&#91;137&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-NYT_Criticized_138-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NYT_Criticized-138">&#91;138&#93;</a></sup> Some readers additionally felt that by claiming he was "horrified" by Rapp's story, Spacey was attempting to paint himself as the victim of the alleged abuse.<sup id="cite_ref-139" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-139">&#91;139&#93;</a></sup> In October 2022, Spacey expressed regret over the way he came out and said that it was "never [his] intention" to deflect from the allegations against him or conflate them with his sexual orientation.<sup id="cite_ref-140" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-140">&#91;140&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-141" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-141">&#91;141&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Reaction_and_ramifications">Reaction and ramifications</span></h3>
<p>Amid the allegations, filming was suspended on the sixth and final season of <i>House of Cards</i>. The show's production company had implemented "an anonymous complaint hotline, crisis counselors, and sexual harassment legal advisors for the crew", and stated that in 2012, "someone on the crew shared a complaint about a specific remark and gesture made by Kevin Spacey. Immediate action was taken following our review of the situation and we are confident the issue was resolved promptly to the satisfaction of all involved."<sup id="cite_ref-142" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-142">&#91;142&#93;</a></sup> According to the production company, Spacey "willingly participated in a training process and since that time MRC has not been made aware of any other complaints" involving him.<sup id="cite_ref-CNNMoney_143-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CNNMoney-143">&#91;143&#93;</a></sup> The show had been due to end in 2018.<sup id="cite_ref-Telegraph_301017_125-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Telegraph_301017-125">&#91;125&#93;</a></sup> The season was shortened from 13 episodes to eight, and Spacey was removed from the cast and from his role as executive producer.<sup id="cite_ref-:0_144-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:0-144">&#91;144&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The <a href="/wiki/Gore_Vidal" title="Gore Vidal">Gore Vidal</a> biographical film <i>Gore</i>, starring Spacey, which was set to be distributed by Netflix, was canceled,<sup id="cite_ref-HR_Stanhope_145-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-HR_Stanhope-145">&#91;145&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-Variety_Nov3_Oldham_146-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Variety_Nov3_Oldham-146">&#91;146&#93;</a></sup> and Netflix went on to sever all ties with him.<sup id="cite_ref-BBC_Sever_147-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BBC_Sever-147">&#91;147&#93;</a></sup> He was due to appear in <i>All the Money in the World</i> as industrialist <a href="/wiki/J._Paul_Getty" title="J. Paul Getty">J. Paul Getty</a>; his scenes were cut and <a href="/wiki/Christopher_Plummer" title="Christopher Plummer">Christopher Plummer</a> replaced him as Getty in reshoots.<sup id="cite_ref-DeadlineA_081117_68-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-DeadlineA_081117-68">&#91;68&#93;</a></sup> In an interview with <i><a href="/wiki/Variety_(magazine)" title="Variety (magazine)">Variety</a></i>, Plummer said, "It's really not replacing [Spacey]. It's starting all over again." Plummer elaborated saying, "I think it's very sad what happened to him... Kevin is such a talented and a terrifically gifted actor, and it's so sad. It's such a shame. That's all I can say, because that's it."<sup id="cite_ref-148" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-148">&#91;148&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>The <a href="/wiki/International_Academy_of_Television_Arts_and_Sciences" title="International Academy of Television Arts and Sciences">International Academy of Television Arts and Sciences</a> reversed its decision to honor Spacey with the 2017 <a href="/wiki/International_Emmy_Founders_Award" title="International Emmy Founders Award">International Emmy Founders Award</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-149" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-149">&#91;149&#93;</a></sup> On November 2, 2017, <i><a href="/wiki/Variety_(magazine)" title="Variety (magazine)">Variety</a></i> reported that his publicist Staci Wolfe and talent agency <a href="/wiki/Creative_Artists_Agency" title="Creative Artists Agency">Creative Artists Agency</a> were ending their relationships with him.<sup id="cite_ref-Variety_Nov2_Nyren_150-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Variety_Nov2_Nyren-150">&#91;150&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-CNNMoney_143-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CNNMoney-143">&#91;143&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Christmas_Eve_YouTube_videos">Christmas Eve YouTube videos</span></h3>
<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1066479718"/><table class="infobox" style="float: right; clear: right; margin:0 0 1.5em 1.5em"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" class="infobox-above" style="font-size:115%">External video</th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="infobox-full-data" style="text-align: left"><img alt="video icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/16px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png" decoding="async" width="16" height="16" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/24px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/32px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="128" data-file-height="128" /> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JZveA-NAIDI">"Let Me Be Frank"</a>, in 2018</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="infobox-full-data" style="text-align: left"><img alt="video icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/16px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png" decoding="async" width="16" height="16" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/24px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/32px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="128" data-file-height="128" /> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WCuuKhjLB0Q">"KTWK"</a>, in 2019</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="infobox-full-data" style="text-align: left"><img alt="video icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/16px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png" decoding="async" width="16" height="16" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/24px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg/32px-Nuvola_apps_kaboodle.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="128" data-file-height="128" /> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w6_N8uxJQ3g&amp;t=1s">"1-800 XMAS"</a>, in 2020</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>From 2018 to 2020, Spacey posted an annual video to his YouTube channel on Christmas Eve.<sup id="cite_ref-151" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-151">&#91;151&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>On December 24, 2018, Spacey uploaded a video titled "Let Me Be Frank", in which he – while in character as Frank Underwood – appeared to deny the real-life allegations leveled against him. The video was described as "bizarre", "stomach-churning", and "creepy".<sup id="cite_ref-152" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-152">&#91;152&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-153" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-153">&#91;153&#93;</a></sup> As of December 2022, the video has over 13&#160;million views.<sup id="cite_ref-154" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-154">&#91;154&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-155" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-155">&#91;155&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>One year later, on December 24, 2019, Spacey posted another video, titled "KTWK" (short for "kill them with kindness"), to his YouTube channel, once again in character as Underwood.<sup id="cite_ref-156" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-156">&#91;156&#93;</a></sup> In 2020, Spacey posted a third Christmas Eve video, titled "1-800 XMAS", in which he spoke in Underwood's accent before <a href="/wiki/Breaking_character" title="Breaking character">breaking character</a> and speaking in his natural voice. He then expressed sympathy for people struggling amidst the <a href="/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic" title="COVID-19 pandemic">COVID-19 pandemic</a> and promoted two suicide and <a href="/wiki/Crisis_hotline" title="Crisis hotline">substance abuse hotlines</a>. The annual videos have been described as "tone-deaf" by Eric Hegedus in the <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Post" title="New York Post">New York Post</a></i> with respect to the allegations against him.<sup id="cite_ref-157" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-157">&#91;157&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>Spacey did not release a new video on Christmas Eve in 2021, or in 2022.<sup id="cite_ref-158" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-158">&#91;158&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Legal_issues">Legal issues</span></h3>
<p>The Los Angeles District Attorney's office stated in April 2018 that it would investigate an allegation that Spacey had sexually assaulted an adult male in 1992.<sup id="cite_ref-159" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-159">&#91;159&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-160" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-160">&#91;160&#93;</a></sup> In July 2018, three more allegations of sexual assault against Spacey were revealed by <a href="/wiki/Scotland_Yard" title="Scotland Yard">Scotland Yard</a>, bringing the total number of open investigations in the UK to six.<sup id="cite_ref-161" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-161">&#91;161&#93;</a></sup> In September 2018, a lawsuit filed at <a href="/wiki/Los_Angeles_Superior_Court" class="mw-redirect" title="Los Angeles Superior Court">Los Angeles Superior Court</a> claimed that Spacey sexually assaulted an unnamed <a href="/wiki/Masseur" class="mw-redirect" title="Masseur">masseur</a> at a house in <a href="/wiki/Malibu,_California" title="Malibu, California">Malibu, California</a>, in October 2016.<sup id="cite_ref-162" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-162">&#91;162&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>In December 2018, Spacey was charged with a felony for allegedly sexually assaulting journalist Heather Unruh's 18-year-old son in <a href="/wiki/Nantucket" title="Nantucket">Nantucket</a>, <a href="/wiki/Massachusetts" title="Massachusetts">Massachusetts</a>, in July 2016.<sup id="cite_ref-kpbs.org_163-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-kpbs.org-163">&#91;163&#93;</a></sup> Spacey pleaded not guilty to the charge on January 7, 2019.<sup id="cite_ref-164" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-164">&#91;164&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-165" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-165">&#91;165&#93;</a></sup> Unruh's son told police he was texting with his girlfriend throughout the alleged "groping" incident. Spacey's defense attorneys spent months trying to obtain copies of the texts and the phone itself. In mid-May 2019, Unruh's son's personal attorney informed the court that the cell phone in question is "missing".<sup id="cite_ref-masslive_166-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-masslive-166">&#91;166&#93;</a></sup> On June 4, 2019, the defense learned that when Unruh gave her son's cell phone to police in 2017, she admitted she had deleted some of the text messages.<sup id="cite_ref-masslive_166-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-masslive-166">&#91;166&#93;</a></sup> Later that month, her son filed a lawsuit against Spacey, claiming emotional damages. On July 5, 2019, he voluntarily dismissed the claims with <a href="/wiki/Prejudice_(law)" class="mw-redirect" title="Prejudice (law)">prejudice</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-167" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-167">&#91;167&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>On July 17, 2019, the criminal assault charge against Spacey was dropped by the <a href="/wiki/Cape_Cod" title="Cape Cod">Cape and Islands</a> prosecutors.<sup id="cite_ref-:1_168-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-:1-168">&#91;168&#93;</a></sup> When the anonymous massage therapist who accused him died, the last remaining criminal case against Spacey was closed.<sup id="cite_ref-169" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-169">&#91;169&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>On September 9, 2020, <a href="/wiki/Anthony_Rapp" title="Anthony Rapp">Anthony Rapp</a> accused Spacey in a complaint about actions that allegedly happened in 1986 (sexual assault and sexual battery) and intentional infliction of emotional distress under the Child Victims Act, which extended New York's <a href="/wiki/Statute_of_limitations" title="Statute of limitations">statute of limitations</a> for suits related to <a href="/wiki/Child_sexual_abuse" title="Child sexual abuse">child sexual abuse</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Rapp_123-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Rapp-123">&#91;123&#93;</a></sup> Joining Rapp in the suit against Spacey was a man who requested to remain anonymous who accused Spacey of sexually abusing him in 1983, when he was 14 and Spacey was 24.<sup id="cite_ref-170" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-170">&#91;170&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-171" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-171">&#91;171&#93;</a></sup> On June 17, 2021, the anonymous accuser was dismissed from the case due to his refusal to publicly identify himself.<sup id="cite_ref-172" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-172">&#91;172&#93;</a></sup> As Rapp's <a href="/wiki/Trial" title="Trial">trial</a> lawsuit against Spacey commenced in October 2022, it was revealed that he had given an inaccurate description of the apartment where he alleged the abuse took place.<sup id="cite_ref-173" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-173">&#91;173&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-174" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-174">&#91;174&#93;</a></sup> On October 17, the judge dismissed the emotional distress charges due to them being a "duplicate" of the battery charges.<sup id="cite_ref-LangFerme_15-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-LangFerme-15">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> On October 20, a jury found Spacey not liable.<sup id="cite_ref-175" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-175">&#91;175&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-176" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-176">&#91;176&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>In 2020, Spacey and his production companies M. Profitt Productions and Trigger Street Productions were ordered to pay $31 million to MRC, the studio that produced <i>House of Cards</i>, for violating its sexual harassment policy.<sup id="cite_ref-177" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-177">&#91;177&#93;</a></sup> Spacey appealed to have the arbitration award overturned, but the request was denied on August 4, 2022.<sup id="cite_ref-178" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-178">&#91;178&#93;</a></sup>
</p><p>On May 26, 2022, Spacey was charged by the <a href="/wiki/Crown_Prosecution_Service" title="Crown Prosecution Service">Crown Prosecution Service</a> (<b>CPS</b>) in the <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a> with four counts of sexual assault against three complainants. The alleged offenses occurred between 2005 and 2013 in <a href="/wiki/London" title="London">London</a> and <a href="/wiki/Gloucestershire" title="Gloucestershire">Gloucestershire</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-179" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-179">&#91;179&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-180" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-180">&#91;180&#93;</a></sup> According to the Crown Prosecution Service, it would be possible to formally charge Spacey only if he entered England or Wales, which would entail <a href="/wiki/Extradition" title="Extradition">extradition</a> if Spacey refused to do so voluntarily.<sup id="cite_ref-181" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-181">&#91;181&#93;</a></sup> Nevertheless, in a statement to <i><a href="/wiki/Good_Morning_America" title="Good Morning America">Good Morning America</a></i> on May 31, 2022, Spacey said that he would "voluntarily appear in the U.K. as soon as can be arranged".<sup id="cite_ref-182" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-182">&#91;182&#93;</a></sup> In his first British court appearance on June 16, Spacey denied the allegations against him.<sup id="cite_ref-183" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-183">&#91;183&#93;</a></sup> On July 14, 2022, Spacey pleaded not guilty to the charges in London. He is due to face trial beginning June 6, 2023.<sup id="cite_ref-184" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-184">&#91;184&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-185" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-185">&#91;185&#93;</a></sup> On November 16, 2022, the CPS authorized an additional seven charges against Spacey, all related to a single complainant arising from incidents alleged to have occurred between 2001 and 2004.<sup id="cite_ref-nbc-spacey-nov2022_186-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-nbc-spacey-nov2022-186">&#91;186&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-cps-spacey-nov2022_187-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-cps-spacey-nov2022-187">&#91;187&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
